Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{200%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{100%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Break up the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} into a #large bowl{} and combine with the garlic and half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using your hands, mix together well and shape into balls, 2 per person.

Place the balls onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until browned on the outside, ~{12-14%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%g}, the remaining garlic and remaining North Indian style spice mix. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @water{200%ml} for the sauce. Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

When the veggie meatballs are cooked, stir them through the curry sauce.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more @sugar{} if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over your veggie meatball rogan josh, then sprinkle over the coriander to finish.

Enjoy!